Los aeropuestos son las [[es/Manual/Estaciones]] para [[en/Manual/Aircraft#aircraft|airplanes]] y [[en/Manual/Aircraft#helicopters|helicopters]]. Contienen uno o varios hangares en los que los aviones y helicópteros pueden ser comprados y reparados. Para los diferentes tipos de aeropuertos ver más abajo. 
Para aprender cómo construir y gestionar aeropuertos ver [[es/Manual/Construcción de aeropuertos]].

=Aeropuertos pequeños=

==Pequeño==
{{es/Manual/Aeropuerto|Fullname=Aeropuerto pequeño|image=en/Manual/Airport s.png|Entry=|Runways=1|Ramps=2|Heli=1 (en terminal)|size=3 x 4|hangars=1|catchment=4|noise=3}}

Este es el aeropuesto más pequeño del juego. El edificio da servicio a dos aviones a la vez, incluyendo a un único helicoptero. Por su tamaño da problemas de tráfico a líneas aereas ya consolidadas

Puede ser víctima del desastre zeppelin al principio del juego,  aviones jet tienen mediana posibilidad de estrellarse

{{en/-}}

==Intercambio==
{{es/Manual/Aeropuerto|Fullname=Intercambio|image=en/Manual/Commuterairport.png|imagewidth=300px|Entry=1983|Runways=1|Ramps=3|Heli=2|size=4 x 5|hangars=1|catchment=4|noise=4}}

El aeropuerto de intercambio es un nuevo aeropuerto diseñado para contener una pequeña cantidad de aviones de carga y descarga dentro de las ciudades. Aunque más grande y superior al aeropuerto pequeño, los aviones más rápidos pueden estrellarse en el aterrizaje debido a la pista de aterrizaje más pequeña. El rendimiento es mayor que el aeropuerto de ciudad debido a menores tiempos de rodaje, y el rendimiento de dos aeropuertos de intercambio es mayor que el de un aeropuerto internacional.

También utiliza los gráficos de los aeropuertos de su uso posterior, por lo que es una actualización de adaptación a los pequeños aeropuertos con aviones viejos y en las etapas finales del juego. Este aeropuerto tiene un tamaño de 4x5, y tiene tres estaciones de carga con dos helipuertos. 

{{en/-}}

=Aeropuertos Grandes=

==Ciudad==
{{es/Manual/Aeropuerto|Fullname=Ciudad|image=en/Manual/Airport c.png|imagewidth=300px|Entry=1955|Runways=1|Ramps=3|Heli=1 (en terminal)|size=6 x 6|hangars=1|catchment=5|noise=5}}

El aeropuerto de ciudad (llamado aeropuerto grande en el TTD original) está un paso por encima del aeropuerto pequeño. Tiene tres terminales de carga/descarga para aviones y una pista. Puede albergar una buena cantidad de tráfico, pero al disponer de una sóla pista, el número de aviones procesados cae de forma significativa cuando los aviones van a esperar al hangar(depósito) y no pueden despegar de nuevo debido al tráfico.

Este aeropuerto es el primero disponible que puede dar servicio a aviones a reacción, most notably the FFP Dart/Aerospatialle Caravelle. Sin embargo,como resultado, la embergadura del aeropuerto es mayor dado que la pista necesita ser más grande. Este aeropuerto puede además tener un avión y un helicóptero aterrizando simultaneamente, al no estar el helipuerto situado en la pista, sino en las calles de rodaje.

{{en/-}}

==Metropolitan airport==
{{en/Manual/Airport|Fullname=Metropolitan Airport|image=en/Manual/Airport m.png|imagewidth=300px|Entry=1980|Runways=2|Ramps=3|Heli=1 (at terminals)|size=6 x 6|hangars=1|catchment=6|noise=8}}

This is an improved version of the City Airport, and is different in that it has two runways (one for landing aircraft and one for those taking off) so that it can handle more traffic. Also the catchment area is slightly greater. All other features are the same.

This airport can handle much more traffic than the City Airport, but is still inferior to the international airport, as planes that have landed must cross runway two to get to the terminal. This affects planes taking off, and can cause a backup of traffic.

{{en/-}}

=Hub airports=

==International airport==
{{en/Manual/Airport|Fullname=International Airport|image=en/Manual/Airport i.png|imagewidth=300px|Entry=1990|Runways=2|Ramps=6|Heli=2|size=7 x 7|hangars=2|catchment=8|noise=17}}

The International airport is the second-largest airport in OpenTTD. It has two runways, like the Metropolitan Airport, but each runway is on the opposite side of the airport so that planes that are arriving/leaving do not obstruct one another. The terminal can handle up to six planes loading or unloading at once. The airport also has two hangars, so that more planes can be serviced. Three helicopters can land simultaneously, while only two helicopters can load/unload at once.

This airport requires a serious amount of traffic to block, but it can still happen with a lot of traffic, with planes having difficulty moving around the airport, as well as difficulty landing. As a result of this, higher capacity airports have been introduced.
{{en/-}}

==Intercontinental==
{{en/Manual/Airport|Fullname=Intercontinental Airport|image=en/Manual/Intercontinentalairport.png|imagewidth=300px|Entry=2002|Runways=4 (two takeoff, two landing)|Ramps=8|Heli=2|size=11 x 9|hangars=2|catchment=10|noise=25}}

The Intercontinental Airport is now OpenTTD's largest airport. Boasting 4 runways, and an overall footprint of 11x9, it easily dwarfs the International airport. Designed to be the hub of airport services, the airport can have two planes take off and two planes land at any time; it also has two helipads. However, it can still clog at high traffic.

All planes can land at this airport with a low risk of crashing, but that risk is still present. This airport has eight terminals for loading, and two hangars. Aircraft will usually take off from the same side they landed, but can change, depending on how full the terminals are.

{{en/-}}

=Helicopter airports=
==Time limit for helicopters==
When building heliports, you should keep in mind that helicopters become unavailable somewhere between 2030 and 2050. This has the consequence that you can not renew old vehicles and stations with heliports only remain isolated.

To avoid this you can [[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Never expire vehicles|disable expiry or reactivate already expired vehicles]], or use NewGRFs like the [[en/Community/NewGRF/Aviators Aircraft Set]] that don't expire.

==Heliport==
{{en/Manual/Airport|Fullname=Heliport|image=en/Manual/Heliport.png|Entry=1963|Runways=N/A|Ramps=N/A|Heli=1|size=1 x 1|hangars=N/A|catchment=4|noise=1}}

Only helicopters can land at a heliport and only 1 helicopter at a time can load or unload (like with the Small Airport). The heliport occupies only 1 tile, so it is very convenient for use inside a crowded city. The heliport is one of the three original airports in the original TTD, introduced for helicopters to load and unload inside cities.

{{en/-}}

==Helidepot==
{{en/Manual/Airport|Fullname=Helidepot|image=en/Manual/Helidepot.png|Entry=1976|Runways=N/A|Ramps=N/A|Heli=1|size=2 x 2|hangars=1|catchment=4|noise=2}}

The Helidepot is similar to a heliport, except it is not a tall building, but more like an airport. It also has one hangar, making this suitable for placing inside cities, and removes the need to build an airport for a simple helicopter route.

{{en/-}}

==Helistation==
{{en/Manual/Airport|Fullname=Helistation|image=en/Manual/Helistation.png|Entry=1980|Runways=N/A|Ramps=N/A|Heli=3|size=2 x 4|hangars=1|catchment=4|noise=3}}

The Helistation, quite simply, is a larger version of the Helidepot, with three helipads instead of one.

{{en/-}}

=Crash landing=
Airplanes have a small chance (0.07%) of crashing each time they land at an airport. Big planes have a high chance (5%) to crash in ''small'' or ''commuter'' airports.  Keep this in mind when building small airports!

See the [[en/Manual/Base Set/Aircraft/Air Comparison|air comparison]] table for a list of "small" airplanes that can be safely landed in small airports.

=Airport Noise=
If the patch option "Airport placement controlled by noise level" (available since [[en/Archive/OpenTTD/OpenTTD 0.7.0]]) is activated, the number of airports which can be placed in the vicinity of a town is not fixed anymore. Instead it depends upon the noise level of the airports, their distance to the town centre and the town's attitude.

The noise level added is the noise level given in the airport description less a distance modificator. The distance modificator is distance divided by (8 + 4 * council's permissiveness (0 for permissive, 1 for tolerant, 2 for hostile). The minimum increase in noise level is at least one per airport.

The town's maximum permitted noise level is 3 plus the population divided by a constant. The constant is settable through the openttd.cfg file, and defaults to 800 for permissive, 2000 for tolerant, and 4000 for hostile
